                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7748: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-10-15T11:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 15, 1926—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 15—3: 50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>481. My 472, October 12, 5 p.m. Following from American consul general, Hankow:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“October 14, 3 p.m. French gunboat <hi rend="italic">Alerte</hi> fired
                            upon yesterday near Wusüeh, killing one sailor, seriously injuring
                            another. <hi rend="italic">Alerte</hi> fired upon again below Hankow
                            this morning but no casualties. Fire returned both times.</p>
                        <p>Conditions at Wuchang continue to improve. Shops are opening and food
                            supplies ample. About 400 bodies inside and outside walls in crude
                            coffins now awaiting burial. All Northern troops evacuated.</p>
                        <p>No change in the situation at Kiukiang.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
